
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-dime-load-09.txt'>
    <title>"Diameter Load Information Conveyance", Ben Campbell, Steve Donovan, Jean-Jacques Trottin</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-dime-load-09.txt</link>
    <description>RFC7068 describes requirements for Overload Control in Diameter. This includes a requirement to allow Diameter nodes to send "load" information, even when the node is not overloaded.  RFC7683 (Diameter Overload Information Conveyance (DOIC)) solution describes a mechanism meeting most of the requirements, but does not currently include the ability to send load information.  This document defines a mechanism for conveying of Diameter load information.</description>
    <dc:date>2017-03-22T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
